    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so u basically think the secular legal framework should always come first? like, if a group's core religious identity is at stake, they just have to accept being forced to do things that violate their conscience for the sake of the \"system\"? isn't that actually kind of a violation of religious freedom itself?",
